<br>
From a personal standpoint, if I take into consideration the amout of free time I spend on EQ having fun for $10.00 a month and try to compare that to other activities I do to have fun (Snowboarding, mountain biking, running, watching a movie, going out to dinner or having drinks with friends) and the cost of those activities, I find that I have an extremely large value for my time spent on EQ. About the only things that really compare with the cost of EQ is reading. But even then, I'm more than capable of reading more than one book a month if I spend as much time reading as I do playing EQ and very shortly the cost of the books themselves will start to cost more than $10.00 a month.<br>
<br>
At $40.00 a month, things start to compare but even then, if I spent as much time on other entertaining activities as I do on EQ, I still feel that the cost will top $40.00 a month.<br>
<br>
Do I disagree that the game could be improved? No. I disagree with people who comment that they should have all this and more available for them at the low cost of $10.00 per month.<br>
<br>
Just my view of things. <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=9396">Bodhi Kierstaad</A>: Warder of Saryrn
